Seal the area!

230
00:21:30,605 --> 00:21:32,516
It's going! Take cover!

231
00:21:32,925 --> 00:21:35,075
-It's gonna blow!
-Don't look at it!

232
00:21:35,245 --> 00:21:37,395
Move! Move!

233
00:21:58,565 --> 00:22:01,398
IJust kept running and running.
I must have run 10 miles.

234
00:22:01,565 --> 00:22:04,637
I have no idea.
IJust wanted to get away from them.

235
00:22:07,245 --> 00:22:09,964
Hey! Help!

236
00:22:11,645 --> 00:22:14,796
By now l was in such a state of shock,
l was panicky.

237
00:22:14,965 --> 00:22:18,116
I couldn 't remember anything,
couldn 't remember what happened.

238
00:22:18,285 --> 00:22:20,594
I forgot l was invisible.

239
00:22:48,365 --> 00:22:50,321
I'll prove something to you.

240
00:22:57,565 --> 00:22:59,123
Okay?

241
00:22:59,285 --> 00:23:05,394
You didn't say something to my face,
so l got something to say to your face.

242
00:23:05,565 --> 00:23:06,759
I--

243
00:23:07,485 --> 00:23:11,478
You can't fire me.
Well, l'll fight you. You can't fire me.

244
00:23:11,645 --> 00:23:15,001
I'll fire you, so come on,
to my face, say it.

245
00:23:15,165 --> 00:23:19,158
So, what's up? Just say it to my face.
I'll get you two back.

246
00:23:19,325 --> 00:23:23,113
You can't fire me!
l'll fire you back!

247
00:23:24,925 --> 00:23:26,358
Taxi!

248
00:23:29,685 --> 00:23:32,563
Can you take me to San Francisco?

249
00:23:34,845 --> 00:23:36,563
Sure.

250
00:23:59,725 --> 00:24:02,603
I'm gonna need some money upfront.

251
00:24:12,605 --> 00:24:14,482
Here. Here you go.

252
00:24:19,325 --> 00:24:23,682
I'm gonna take a catnap. Can you wake
me up when we get to the bridge?

253
00:24:29,245 --> 00:24:33,921
The first thing l had to do was call
my doctor. No, no. That was stupid.

254
00:24:34,085 --> 00:24:37,839
How would an internist help me?
l needed a goddamn magician.

255
00:24:39,885 --> 00:24:42,797
Excuse me. Is this a cab?

256
00:24:44,445 --> 00:24:49,883
-Did you say something?
-Yes. Sacramento and Powell.

257
00:25:01,245 --> 00:25:04,396
Hey, could you pull over here?

258
00:25:27,325 --> 00:25:33,116
-Oh, God.
-Oh, l'm sorry. Oh, God.

259
00:25:36,525 --> 00:25:38,356
Oh, baby.

260
00:25:40,325 --> 00:25:44,921
Driver, could you take me to San Rafael,
please? l changed my mind.

261
00:26:02,365 --> 00:26:06,074
I had to get into my apartment,
where l could study myself...

262
00:26:06,245 --> 00:26:08,361
...figure out what had happened.

263
00:26:23,765 --> 00:26:27,963
Maybe it would wear off in a couple
of days, but what if it didn 't?

264
00:26:28,125 --> 00:26:30,878
What if l evaporated into nothing?

265
00:26:43,965 --> 00:26:47,116
He may have overheard something
that made him apprehensive.

266
00:26:47,485 --> 00:26:51,444
-The explosion might have frightened him.
-Anything could happen to him.

267
00:26:51,605 --> 00:26:53,516
He may be dead already.

268
00:26:53,685 --> 00:26:58,201
Well, l'm gonna have to take this up
with Parcells at Langley.

269
00:26:59,645 --> 00:27:02,034
I don't think you want to do that.

270
00:27:06,845 --> 00:27:10,121
-What do you mean?
-Show him the data. Give him anything. . .

271
00:27:10,285 --> 00:27:15,723
. . .but say nothing about the man.
Let's keep this private, huh?

272
00:27:16,605 --> 00:27:18,516
Now, think about it.

273
00:27:18,845 --> 00:27:23,282
You say one word, it becomes the deputy
director's show and not yours anymore.

274
00:27:23,445 --> 00:27:25,481
We're out of the loop.

275
00:27:26,125 --> 00:27:31,074
On the other hand, if we grab him quick,
we become his control.

276
00:27:31,245 --> 00:27:33,839
We're the only ones that know he exists.

277
00:27:34,005 --> 00:27:38,317
The single most exotic intelligence asset
on the planet is ours. . .

278
00:27:39,005 --> 00:27:40,916
. . .and ours alone.

279
00:27:41,245 --> 00:27:43,122
What do you need?

280
00:27:44,445 --> 00:27:48,438
--noon at an apartment in the 300 block
of South Jefferson in Daly City.

281
00:27:48,605 --> 00:27:52,598
The mother said she left her son
in Murphy's care for a few hours.

282
00:27:52,765 --> 00:27:54,118
Murphy lived in....

283
00:27:54,285 --> 00:27:57,721
Felt like l hadn 't eaten in a week,
which is easier said than done...

284
00:27:57,885 --> 00:28:00,524
... when you can 't even
see your own hands.

285
00:28:02,685 --> 00:28:07,475
Fire officials say the blaze
was caused by a faulty space heater...

286
00:28:07,645 --> 00:28:10,523
...in the second-floor apartment
on Diego Street.

287
00:28:10,685 --> 00:28:14,473
The single-family unit
was being shared by eight people.

288
00:28:14,645 --> 00:28:19,799
The heat had been turned off for
three weeks for failure to pay a gas bill.

289
00:28:19,965 --> 00:28:23,640
There was an accident today
at the Magnascopics Laboratory.

290
00:28:23,805 --> 00:28:26,365
A spokesman
for the nuclear regulatory agency says:

291
00:28:26,525 --> 00:28:30,598
"Although the laboratory was the site
of nuclear-fusion research...

292
00:28:30,765 --> 00:28:34,804
... there was no radioactive material
and no risk of contamination. "

293
00:28:34,965 --> 00:28:37,354
-No inJuries were reported.
-Bullshit.

294
00:28:37,525 --> 00:28:41,438
Authorities are keeping the area
cordoned off as a precaution.

295
00:28:41,605 --> 00:28:44,119
An Oregon man
is being arraigned today...

296
00:28:44,285 --> 00:28:47,322
...on charges he killed a man
nine years ago....

297
00:28:47,485 --> 00:28:49,680
Oh, Jesus.

298
00:29:08,045 --> 00:29:11,117
-What happened?
-Where have you been?

299
00:29:11,285 --> 00:29:14,277
For a moment,
l thought it had all been a dream.

300
00:29:14,445 --> 00:29:16,163
But that didn 't last.

301
00:29:16,325 --> 00:29:19,954
I saw the news about the fire
at Magnascopics and l was worried.

302
00:29:20,125 --> 00:29:23,117
The food l hadn 't thrown up
the night before had evaporated.

303
00:29:23,285 --> 00:29:24,843
I was as transparent as ever.

304
00:29:25,005 --> 00:29:28,202
-Oh, shit.
-Nick. Nick.

305
00:29:28,365 --> 00:29:30,083
I'm here.

306
00:29:31,605 --> 00:29:33,960
-Sort of.
-So, what happened out there?

307
00:29:35,325 --> 00:29:39,159
Cathy, l've been sick as a dog.
What's this about a fire?

308
00:29:39,325 --> 00:29:44,274
You didn't go, then? You're sick? Well,
l'm sorry. Can l send you some soup?

309
00:29:44,445 --> 00:29:49,519
No. No. No. I'll be fine. Just reschedule
all my appointments for Monday.

310
00:29:49,685 --> 00:29:52,279
-Thanks, Cathy. Bye.
-Bye.

311
00:29:53,885 --> 00:29:55,955
It's Roger. Where are you?

312
00:29:56,125 --> 00:29:59,674
Should we be long or short on Allied?
The stock is going crazy.

313
00:29:59,845 --> 00:30:01,437
Would you call me, please?

314
00:30:05,485 --> 00:30:07,601
Hi, Nick. It's Alice.

315
00:30:07,765 --> 00:30:12,919
I'm calling to confirm our lunch on Friday.
Am l being too forward about this?

316
00:30:13,085 --> 00:30:16,964
What am l talking about? We've already
been to the ladies ' room together.

317
00:30:17,125 --> 00:30:18,240
See you Friday.

318
00:30:21,165 --> 00:30:25,522
Nick. David Jenkins. Global Devices.
Perhaps we met last night.

319
00:30:25,685 --> 00:30:28,802
We got your name from the register.
There will be an inquiry...

320
00:30:28,965 --> 00:30:32,753
...into what happened at Magnascopics
last night. We'll need a signed statement--

321
00:30:33,805 --> 00:30:37,241
I knew that voice.
Who the hell did he think he was kidding?

322
00:30:37,405 --> 00:30:39,282
These guys were fast.

323
00:30:39,445 --> 00:30:41,720
Robin, it's Nick Halloway.
It's important.

324
00:30:41,885 --> 00:30:45,594
Mr. Cebron 's in court today,
but l know he wants to talk to you.

325
00:30:45,765 --> 00:30:49,394
-He does?
-Are you in trouble with the government?

326
00:30:49,565 --> 00:30:52,557
-Why would l be?
-That's what Mr. Cebron asked...

327
00:30:52,725 --> 00:30:55,797
...but they were being real vague.
Oh, can you hold on?

328
00:30:59,405 --> 00:31:01,236
Robin, they're paging my flight.

329
00:31:01,405 --> 00:31:04,522
-Tell him l'll call him when l get to Dallas.
-Dallas?

330
00:31:06,085 --> 00:31:10,601
Who the hell were these guys?
How did they find me so quickly?

331
00:31:12,365 --> 00:31:15,243
I had to get out of there fast.

332
00:31:15,405 --> 00:31:19,318
The first thing l had to do was remember
where l put myJacket and shoes.

333
00:31:53,085 --> 00:31:56,600
Keep that thing low so when l mark him,
you don't get off a headshot.

334
00:31:59,965 --> 00:32:01,956
We're at the front door.

335
00:32:03,925 --> 00:32:05,563
Zebra Team standing by.

336
00:32:05,725 --> 00:32:07,078
-Alpha?
-Ready.

337
00:32:07,245 --> 00:32:08,473
-Delta?
-In place.

338
00:32:09,405 --> 00:32:10,963
-Baker Team?
-Set up.

339
00:32:11,125 --> 00:32:13,719
-You've got a green light.
-Let's take this asshole.

340
00:32:55,965 --> 00:32:59,275
-This is Jenkins. I'm at the front door.
-Shit.

341
00:32:59,445 --> 00:33:01,879
-Give me the status on the roof.
-No movement yet.

342
00:33:04,285 --> 00:33:06,719
Come on, come on, come on.

343
00:33:17,885 --> 00:33:20,035
-Is it all right to open up?
-Yes, ma'am.

344
00:33:20,205 --> 00:33:22,594
May l come in to use
the phone, please?

345
00:33:24,925 --> 00:33:29,521
He seemed such a nice young man,
that Mr. Halloway. Has he killed someone?

346
00:33:35,605 --> 00:33:37,561
Oh, l must have slipped.

347
00:33:44,685 --> 00:33:46,084
Halloway!

348
00:33:51,205 --> 00:33:52,684
I got him.

349
00:34:02,325 --> 00:34:03,314
Oh, shit.

350
00:34:03,485 --> 00:34:05,237
California Street.

351
00:34:12,765 --> 00:34:15,154
Mr. McCaren, you all right, sir?

352
00:34:15,325 --> 00:34:18,840
-What happened?
-I think something hit me.

353
00:34:19,005 --> 00:34:22,122
-What was it? You sure you're okay?
-My back.

354
00:34:23,445 --> 00:34:25,037
Who are you guys?

355
00:34:35,485 --> 00:34:37,476
Halloway, are you there?

356
00:34:40,325 --> 00:34:44,637
If you're hurt,
l'd like to help you.

357
00:34:47,325 --> 00:34:51,603
Halloway, listen to me.
You can't escape.

358
00:34:52,765 --> 00:34:58,044
Believe me. Wherever you go,
whoever you tell, it all comes back to me.

359
00:34:59,725 --> 00:35:04,845
You must trust us, Nick. We're the only
people that can give you your life back.

360
00:35:05,005 --> 00:35:06,358
We're all you have.

361
00:35:09,805 --> 00:35:14,083
It's lonely, isn't it, Nick?
When you're a freak?

362
00:35:14,245 --> 00:35:15,394
Fuck you.

363
00:35:25,565 --> 00:35:27,840
For hours,
l wandered the streets of the city.

364
00:35:28,005 --> 00:35:30,360
I was a fugitive,
afraid of getting caught.

365
00:35:30,525 --> 00:35:34,040
I kept imagining Jenkins leaping out
at me from every dark corner.

366
00:35:38,645 --> 00:35:40,044
Taxi!

367
00:35:47,485 --> 00:35:52,195
As a child, when l'd dream about being
invisible, l thought it would be so easy.

368
00:35:52,365 --> 00:35:56,916
I could do what l want,
go where l want and take what l want.

369
00:35:57,085 --> 00:35:59,041
But that's the catch.

370
00:35:59,205 --> 00:36:03,118
No matter how hungry l was,
l couldn 't give myself away.

371
00:36:08,605 --> 00:36:11,278
My purse! My purse!

372
00:36:19,245 --> 00:36:20,997
I was starving and exhausted.

373
00:36:21,165 --> 00:36:24,077
Somehow, l found myself
in the alley behind my club...

374
00:36:24,245 --> 00:36:27,043
...and l figured it would do
for the time being.

375
00:36:28,965 --> 00:36:32,594
In a building this size,
there would be places to hide.

376
00:36:33,525 --> 00:36:35,993
Finally, l formulated a plan.

377
00:36:37,565 --> 00:36:39,760
I'd get to this Dr. Wachs
from Magnascopics...

378
00:36:39,925 --> 00:36:41,324
...show him what had happened.

379
00:36:41,485 --> 00:36:46,001
And whatever he did to get me this way,
l would demand he undo.

380
00:37:08,685 --> 00:37:11,563
Wachs?
Magnascopics doctor?

381
00:37:11,725 --> 00:37:14,398
Last Wednesday?
l was inside when it happened.

382
00:37:14,565 --> 00:37:18,240
-I beg your pardon?
-Give me a dollar. They could be watching.

383
00:37:18,925 --> 00:37:21,564
Does the word "invisible"
mean anything to you?

384
00:37:26,965 --> 00:37:31,243
-Where's the professor?
-In the park, taking a stroll.

385
00:37:39,725 --> 00:37:42,159
-Come on, will you? We're gonna lose him.
-Relax.

386
00:37:42,565 --> 00:37:47,639
But this is astounding.
I never dreamed. They never told me.

387
00:37:47,805 --> 00:37:49,477
Open your coat,
show me the rest.

388
00:37:49,645 --> 00:37:52,443
-Trust me. It's all the same.
-Oh, dear God.

389
00:37:52,605 --> 00:37:54,994
There's got to be
another psychotron, right?

390
00:37:55,165 --> 00:37:57,395
Can't you just take me there
and turn me back?

391
00:37:57,565 --> 00:38:01,877
I'll forget the whole thing. No lawsuits,
no recriminations. No harm, no foul.

392
00:38:02,045 --> 00:38:06,641
Our research had nothing to do with
invisibility. This was a random reaction.

393
00:38:06,805 --> 00:38:08,921
-Don't say this.
-What are you doing here?

394
00:38:09,085 --> 00:38:11,201
You should be with me,
with us, in the lab.

395
00:38:11,365 --> 00:38:15,040
We must replicate the variables,
begin to explore how this happened.

396
00:38:15,205 --> 00:38:18,242
"Begin to explore"?
That's not good enough!

397
00:38:18,405 --> 00:38:21,158
-You gotta help me now!
-It's gonna take time.

398
00:38:21,325 --> 00:38:25,398
I don't have time! l want
my molecules back! Look at me!

399
00:38:25,565 --> 00:38:26,998
It's him.

400
00:38:31,285 --> 00:38:32,798
-You gotta turn me back.
-No!

401
00:38:34,845 --> 00:38:36,836
Oh, God. You bastards!

402
00:39:07,765 --> 00:39:08,754
Shit!

403
00:39:18,365 --> 00:39:21,835
Would you bring me a phone,
please? Thanks.

404
00:39:25,805 --> 00:39:28,273
Hi, this is Alice Monroe.
I'm meeting Nick...

405
00:39:28,445 --> 00:39:31,005
...for lunch at the Brasserie.
Is he on his way?

406
00:39:31,165 --> 00:39:33,759
I don 't have you in his book
or l would have phoned.

407
00:39:33,925 --> 00:39:36,837
Mr. Halloway's out sick.

408
00:39:38,285 --> 00:39:40,753
-I hope it's nothing serious.
-No, it's the flu.

409
00:39:40,925 --> 00:39:43,120
I'll tell him you called.
What's your number?

410
00:39:43,965 --> 00:39:48,277
Yeah. It's Alice Monroe.
555-9290.

411
00:39:48,445 --> 00:39:49,434
-Sure.
-Thanks.

412
00:39:49,605 --> 00:39:51,323
-Bye.
-Bye.

413
00:39:53,405 --> 00:39:58,115
I guess l'll be eating alone.
Can l see a menu, please? Thanks.

414
00:40:00,125 --> 00:40:03,959
I am the Sidney Leavitt professor
of theoretical physics, a member. . .

415
00:40:04,125 --> 00:40:07,640
-. . .of the National Academy of Science!
-Shut up!

416
00:40:07,805 --> 00:40:12,117
-I'll ask again. Where is he?
-I've already told you, l don't know.

417
00:40:12,285 --> 00:40:14,674
Why didn't somebody tell me
there was a man inside?

418
00:40:14,845 --> 00:40:17,723
When are you planning to make
contact with him again?

419
00:40:17,885 --> 00:40:20,445
Exactly under whose authority
are you operating?

420
00:40:20,605 --> 00:40:24,075
I know the deputy director,
and Dick Parcells would never sanction. . .

421
00:40:24,245 --> 00:40:27,920
. . .that stunt your goons pulled in the park
this afternoon.

422
00:40:28,805 --> 00:40:34,004
Now, Dr. Wachs, what were you
really doing at Magnascopics?

423
00:40:34,165 --> 00:40:37,555
I find it hard to believe
that this was all simply an accident.

424
00:40:37,725 --> 00:40:39,636
I am aghast at this.

425
00:40:39,805 --> 00:40:43,161
There's an invisible man loose in the city.
I want to find him too. . .

426
00:40:43,325 --> 00:40:45,475
. . .so, what are we doing here?

427
00:40:49,885 --> 00:40:53,764
-Take off your jacket.
-Why? What are you gonna do?

428
00:40:53,925 --> 00:40:57,395
Don't worry, doc.
This won't hurt you a bit.

429
00:40:57,565 --> 00:41:00,238
Make a fist.
I said, make a fist.

430
00:41:00,405 --> 00:41:03,363
-Let me know when he's ready.
-Why are you doing this to me?

431
00:41:03,525 --> 00:41:07,962
-All l know is that he exists.
-And that's already too much.

432
00:41:08,805 --> 00:41:12,161
"Never been married,
parents both deceased. "

433
00:41:12,325 --> 00:41:15,954
The guy's got a few friends,
but not real close to any of them.

434
00:41:16,125 --> 00:41:21,074
Not exactly a workaholic either.
He kind of plays it fast and loose.

435
00:41:21,245 --> 00:41:23,713
It's always difficult
with people like this.

436
00:41:23,885 --> 00:41:28,754
No strong emotional ties,
no political beliefs, no particular interests.

437
00:41:29,885 --> 00:41:33,195
As a matter of fact,
when you think about it. . .

438
00:41:33,365 --> 00:41:38,439
. . .the man has the perfect profile.
He was invisible before he was invisible.

439
00:41:38,605 --> 00:41:44,760
Look, he's not a pro. He's alone.
He's desperate. He'll crack.

440
00:41:47,645 --> 00:41:50,079
Where are you hiding, Halloway?

441
00:42:14,525 --> 00:42:16,834
I could only sleep
out of sheer exhaustion.

442
00:42:17,005 --> 00:42:19,917
And when l did sleep, l would dream.
Weird, crazy dreams...

443
00:42:20,085 --> 00:42:23,964
...about what might have been
and what l had lost.

444
00:42:24,125 --> 00:42:25,956
Welcome, Nick.

445
00:42:28,885 --> 00:42:31,843
-Oh, Nick. Hi.
-Hello, Nick.

446
00:42:32,005 --> 00:42:34,644
Nick, good to see you.
Good to see you.

447
00:42:34,805 --> 00:42:36,477
Hi, Nick.

448
00:42:37,085 --> 00:42:38,404
Hi, Nick.

449
00:42:40,885 --> 00:42:44,116
-Nick, you charmer.
-Right this way.

450
00:43:35,845 --> 00:43:37,403
Looking for something, Nick?

451
00:43:51,965 --> 00:43:56,277
It was about time l did look for something.
Maybe l could turn the tables on them.

452
00:43:56,445 --> 00:44:00,199
Find out what they knew about
my condition and use it to my advantage.

453
00:44:25,805 --> 00:44:27,955
-Who's up?
-Vinny's up. Sit down and deal.

454
00:44:28,125 --> 00:44:30,685
Yeah. I owe the pot $2.

455
00:44:32,445 --> 00:44:34,675
Red dog, red dog,
face of red dog.

456
00:44:34,845 --> 00:44:38,042
Nothing is wild, and it starts with Vin.
Six dollars in the pot.

457
00:44:39,965 --> 00:44:41,717
Pass? No pass?

458
00:45:23,685 --> 00:45:27,121
Congressman Davis called
for a third time.

459
00:45:28,125 --> 00:45:31,959
Singleton called from L.A. Iooking
for Wachs. I said what you told me to.

460
00:45:32,125 --> 00:45:34,161
If we can't find this dude
for six months. . .

461
00:45:34,325 --> 00:45:37,317
. . .is he gonna keep us
operational that long?

462
00:45:37,485 --> 00:45:42,240
Singleton's weak and he's unreliable,
but he knows the value of the prize.

463
00:45:42,405 --> 00:45:45,124
So let's start
with surveillance reports.

464
00:45:45,285 --> 00:45:47,924
-Comments?
-Okay, phone calls. . . .

465
00:46:41,021 --> 00:46:42,420
Welcome.

466
00:46:47,501 --> 00:46:51,380
I often sit here like this
at the end of the day, in darkness. . .

467
00:46:51,541 --> 00:46:56,296
. . .and imagine what it must be like.
Were you conscious when it happened?

468
00:46:57,261 --> 00:47:02,540
Did you feel yourself change?
Did you pray?

469
00:47:05,421 --> 00:47:09,573
I've been worried about you, Nick.
Is everything all right?

470
00:47:15,301 --> 00:47:17,576
How long have you been here?

471
00:47:18,221 --> 00:47:22,931
Long enough to learn things about you
l might tell my friends at the Chronicle.

472
00:47:25,581 --> 00:47:28,379
You don't have any friends
at the Chronicle, Nick.

473
00:47:29,301 --> 00:47:31,974
Besides, we both know that
when you go to the press. . .

474
00:47:32,141 --> 00:47:34,609
. . .you become the last thing
you want to be:

475
00:47:34,781 --> 00:47:36,612
A circus attraction.

476
00:47:36,781 --> 00:47:39,454
-Now, l told you. It all comes back to me.
-Bullshit.

477
00:47:41,021 --> 00:47:43,535
You answer to people.
I heard.

478
00:47:43,701 --> 00:47:47,330
Maybe l'll call Washington
and talk to a guy named Singleton.

479
00:47:48,061 --> 00:47:49,414
Let's say you do.

480
00:47:49,581 --> 00:47:54,336
What do you think you could control the
moment you make your presence known?

481
00:47:55,141 --> 00:47:59,180
And if l work with you,
l suppose things would be different.

482
00:47:59,341 --> 00:48:03,459
I could come and go as l please.
Put your goddamn hands on the desk!

483
00:48:05,461 --> 00:48:10,899
Now get a grip on yourself, Nick.
Listen to what we're offering you.

484
00:48:11,061 --> 00:48:15,976
-In exchange for what?
-For your services to your country.

485
00:48:16,661 --> 00:48:21,530
You have a wider obligation now.
You can be of immeasurable value to us.

486
00:48:23,581 --> 00:48:25,378
I'm not doing your spying.

487
00:48:26,141 --> 00:48:30,578
Suppose we'd had you,
an invisible agent, in 1 939.

488
00:48:30,741 --> 00:48:33,733
Maybe there wouldn't
have been a Second World War.

489
00:48:33,901 --> 00:48:37,416
What are you saying? You mean
l would have killed Hitler for you?

490
00:48:37,581 --> 00:48:43,497
I mean maybe you could have saved
30 million lives. Changed history.

491
00:48:43,661 --> 00:48:49,372
Now, assassination, anything at all, is
entirely ethical if you're on the right side.

492
00:48:56,301 --> 00:48:58,940
Now you listen to me,
you son of a bitch.

493
00:48:59,101 --> 00:49:02,696
I've lost everything but my soul,
and you won't take that away from me.

494
00:49:02,861 --> 00:49:06,695
Whatever l become, it'll be my choice,
not yours. Is that clear?

495
00:49:06,861 --> 00:49:10,217
We're prepared to give you
anything you want, everything you need.

496
00:49:10,381 --> 00:49:16,616
But you have to understand, if you
won't work with us, l can't let you live.

497
00:49:18,061 --> 00:49:21,895
I don't sleep well. I can see through
my eyelids, through the top of my head.

498
00:49:22,061 --> 00:49:23,813
I get walleyed!
l get bat-shit!

499
00:49:29,381 --> 00:49:31,770
Don't you ever touch me again.

500
00:49:39,501 --> 00:49:41,378
I'll kill him. I swear to God.

501
00:49:43,301 --> 00:49:46,850
-Back off.
-Do what he says.

502
00:49:49,141 --> 00:49:50,540
Move it.

503
00:49:57,581 --> 00:49:58,650
Nick.

504
00:49:59,581 --> 00:50:04,894
Contrary to what you might think,
l am not without feelings.

505
00:50:06,901 --> 00:50:10,655
Oh, God. Don't you see, we're
in this together, Nick, you and l?

506
00:50:10,821 --> 00:50:14,177
We're not so terribly different.
We're iconoclasts.

507
00:50:15,621 --> 00:50:17,930
Think of the adventure
we could have together.

508
00:50:18,101 --> 00:50:20,774
Yeah, we can go to Frontierland.

509
00:50:27,261 --> 00:50:30,059
-See you, Dave.
-Oh, Nick--

510
00:50:39,181 --> 00:50:40,580
Give me that.

511
00:50:49,501 --> 00:50:51,492
I had to get out of San Francisco.

512
00:50:51,661 --> 00:50:55,336
Jenkins would never stop searching,
and l wasn 't safe at the Academy Club.

513
00:50:55,501 --> 00:50:59,335
He knew my patterns. It'd only be a
matter of time before he'd catch me there.

514
00:50:59,501 --> 00:51:02,095
There were hotels,
but they would be more dangerous.

515
00:51:02,261 --> 00:51:06,539
I couldn 't go back to my apartment,
and l couldn 't risk confiding in anyone.

516
00:51:07,741 --> 00:51:10,699
That's when l decided
on George's summerhouse.

517
00:51:12,141 --> 00:51:16,339
Three quarts of vodka, 3 quarts of
Scotch. Do you have any bouillon cubes?

518
00:51:16,501 --> 00:51:20,733
Yeah, for soup or broth.
You know, chicken, beef, vegetable.

519
00:51:21,221 --> 00:51:26,693
Well, which is clearest? Clearest.
Which is most transparent?

520
00:51:26,861 --> 00:51:30,820
I'm looking for clear foods here.
No coloring. Easy to digest.

521
00:51:30,981 --> 00:51:34,212
My doctor says l gotta eat
clear foods. I'm all gas.

522
00:51:34,661 --> 00:51:37,255
Hold on a minute, will you?
What's that, George?

523
00:51:39,341 --> 00:51:43,812
Mr. Talbot says, could you please charge it
to his account? 37 Beachfront Lane.

524
00:51:43,981 --> 00:51:47,860
Thank you very much. Yeah,
tell the kid to come in the front door.

525
00:51:49,741 --> 00:51:51,652
Anybody home?

526
00:52:24,461 --> 00:52:25,894
Hello?

527
00:52:44,661 --> 00:52:46,060
Hey, dickwad.

528
00:52:54,381 --> 00:52:56,736
I had to put the old Nick Halloway
behind me.

529
00:52:59,541 --> 00:53:02,135
I'd create a new identity,
go underground.

530
00:53:02,701 --> 00:53:03,895
-Morning.
-Morning.

531
00:53:04,061 --> 00:53:07,497
Get myself a secure place
where Jenkins would never find me.

532
00:53:08,901 --> 00:53:10,539
I could play the market
by phone.

533
00:53:10,701 --> 00:53:15,138
All l needed was a name on a brokerage
account and a few bucks to start with.

534
00:53:15,301 --> 00:53:18,259
I would become the invisible tycoon,
and then....

535
00:53:18,421 --> 00:53:20,412
Then l would make them pay.
All of them.

536
00:53:20,581 --> 00:53:24,654
They would rue the day
they tangled with Nick Halloway.

537
00:53:37,101 --> 00:53:38,693
Wow, George. It's beautiful.

538
00:53:38,861 --> 00:53:40,931
Yeah. Everybody needs a place
to get away.

539
00:53:41,101 --> 00:53:43,899
-Recharge the batteries.
-If you can get here.

540
00:53:44,061 --> 00:53:47,417
-We got here, didn't we?
-Yeah, we did, but that traffic. . . .

541
00:53:47,781 --> 00:53:49,339
Now half the day is gone.

542
00:53:53,781 --> 00:53:55,658
Get in. We'll drive
back to the city.

543
00:53:57,501 --> 00:53:59,492
Shit, George.
What are you doing here?

544
00:53:59,661 --> 00:54:03,176
-Just forget it. We're here, all right?
-That's what l said.

545
00:54:03,341 --> 00:54:07,971
God! The silence.
And the air out here.

546
00:54:08,781 --> 00:54:11,739
It makes me think of children
and the Fourth of July.

547
00:54:11,901 --> 00:54:15,337
I like it better in the wintertime.
It gets so crowded in the summer.

548
00:54:15,501 --> 00:54:19,938
This is the first chance l've had to relax
since l've been back. Thanks, George.

549
00:54:20,101 --> 00:54:22,854
It's so stuffy in here.

550
00:54:24,061 --> 00:54:26,814
It smells like somebody had a fire.

551
00:54:32,701 --> 00:54:36,057
-Subletting to someone?
-What the hell is going on?

552
00:54:36,221 --> 00:54:41,011
-I haven't been here since January.
-I think we should have a look around.

553
00:54:42,381 --> 00:54:44,531
Is there a gun in the house?

554
00:55:00,941 --> 00:55:03,057
Goddamn it!

555
00:55:05,421 --> 00:55:07,651
Somebody's been
wearing my clothes!

556
00:55:09,341 --> 00:55:12,014
-This is certainly peculiar.
-What?

557
00:55:12,181 --> 00:55:16,094
Everything's here, my hidden key
is missing, and the Jacuzzi's on the timer.

558
00:55:16,261 --> 00:55:19,810
All right, l don't like this.
This is making me very nervous.

559
00:55:19,981 --> 00:55:22,336
Whoever it is,
they left you fully stocked.

560
00:55:22,621 --> 00:55:24,771
Someone put food
in my refrigerator?

561
00:55:25,141 --> 00:55:28,656
There's some nice stuff in here.
There's a bottle of Montrachet.

562
00:55:28,821 --> 00:55:32,291
That's why l love Marin County.
You get a better class of burglar.

563
00:55:32,461 --> 00:55:36,136
It's gotta be my brother Chuck.
He must have split up with Kathleen again.

564
00:55:36,301 --> 00:55:37,939
Oh, great.

565
00:55:38,101 --> 00:55:41,252
Wyborowa, 1 00 proof.
Chuck drink this?

566
00:55:41,661 --> 00:55:43,060
No.

567
00:55:45,421 --> 00:55:47,935
But l know who does.

568
00:55:49,581 --> 00:55:51,458
Halloway's in trouble.

569
00:55:51,621 --> 00:55:55,375
I spoke to a pencil pusher at some
government agency l never heard of.

570
00:55:55,541 --> 00:55:58,214
He asked me the same
personal questions about Nick. . .

571
00:55:58,381 --> 00:56:01,498
. . .the SEC did when
Charlie Randolph got busted.

572
00:56:01,661 --> 00:56:04,095
There's a lot of confusion over
at Shipway & Whitman.

573
00:56:04,261 --> 00:56:07,492
When a guy's been working there
1 0 years, suddenly disappears. . . .

574
00:56:07,661 --> 00:56:11,017
Roger Whitman's got auditors
looking to see if anything's missing.

575
00:56:11,421 --> 00:56:15,096
Do you really think he's a thief?
Didn't strike me as the embezzler type.

576
00:56:15,261 --> 00:56:19,459
Knowing Nick, he probably came here
to shack up with somebody's wife.

577
00:56:23,341 --> 00:56:27,573
-If that's all it was, he'd have called me.
-Why don't we just change the subject?

578
00:56:27,741 --> 00:56:31,416
Wherever he is, l'm sure Nick would love
to know we're talking about him.

579
00:56:31,581 --> 00:56:33,572
I think Halloway got
in a lot of trouble. . .

580
00:56:33,741 --> 00:56:37,893
. . .came out here, got nice and loaded
and walked into the ocean one day.

581
00:56:38,141 --> 00:56:41,816
Oh, come on. Nick's way too narcissistic
to kill himself.

582
00:56:42,061 --> 00:56:46,054
He'll probably wash up on the shore
one day all bloated and eaten by crabs.

583
00:56:46,221 --> 00:56:47,973
Richard!

584
00:56:48,821 --> 00:56:52,131
How can you say these things?
l thought you were Nick's friends.

585
00:56:52,301 --> 00:56:54,257
It's just--
I don't know.

586
00:56:54,421 --> 00:56:57,538
I got a real funny vibe,
like he's dead.

587
00:56:58,381 --> 00:57:00,770
Well, why don't you have
a séance, Richard.

588
00:57:00,941 --> 00:57:06,652
Get out your Ouija board and call up
his spirit from the dead. I'm going to bed.

589
00:57:08,541 --> 00:57:10,099
George. . . .

590
00:57:10,261 --> 00:57:13,219
Seems to me, if he was gonna
commit suicide in my house. . .

591
00:57:13,381 --> 00:57:17,420
. . .he'd have the common decency to leave
a note or clean up a little first.

592
00:57:17,581 --> 00:57:21,574
Laugh, but l'd be careful mocking
what you don't understand.

593
00:57:21,741 --> 00:57:27,452
Nick! Nick! lf you're here with us,
Nick, give us a sign.

594
00:57:30,941 --> 00:57:33,057
Jesus! You bastard!

595
00:57:34,101 --> 00:57:36,251
He could have been channeling
through me!

596
00:57:38,581 --> 00:57:39,980
Shit!

597
00:57:42,781 --> 00:57:44,533
Losing weight, Richard?

598
00:57:51,901 --> 00:57:56,179
-So much for my good friends.
-Ellen, you wanna get the lights, please?

599
00:57:58,221 --> 00:58:00,940
-Night.
-Good night, you two.

600
00:58:02,381 --> 00:58:07,409
-Well, l'm not really that tired, are you?
-Yeah. I'm exhausted.

601
00:58:07,581 --> 00:58:11,494
Yeah, me too. Meet you on the beach
for a swim, bright and early?

602
00:58:12,541 --> 00:58:14,213
Sure. Sleep well.

603
00:58:20,741 --> 00:58:23,175
I remember feeling
an enormous sense of relief...

604
00:58:23,341 --> 00:58:26,378
... that she didn 't let him
into her room or kiss him.

605
00:58:31,141 --> 00:58:33,097
Alice, are you decent?

606
00:58:36,141 --> 00:58:37,574
Yes.

607
00:58:41,421 --> 00:58:45,812
-What is it?
-I was saving this till l sold my novel.

608
00:58:46,341 --> 00:58:48,536
You're a broker, not a novelist.

609
00:58:48,701 --> 00:58:53,217
Actually, l'm starting it this summer,
but l've got it all worked out in my head.

610
00:58:57,541 --> 00:59:00,613
This is really sweet,
but not tonight. I'm tired.

611
00:59:00,781 --> 00:59:03,818
Oh, just a short one. Come on.

612
00:59:04,301 --> 00:59:06,496
I really admire what you do.

613
00:59:07,021 --> 00:59:09,979
You're so unlike all the other women
l meet. You don't seem. . .

614
00:59:10,141 --> 00:59:12,780
-. . .caught up in the bullshit.
-Not yet anyway.

615
00:59:14,901 --> 00:59:16,459
Richard. . . .

616
00:59:17,461 --> 00:59:20,339
I'm really gonna have to say
good night.

617
00:59:20,501 --> 00:59:22,890
There's something l haven't told you.

618
00:59:23,181 --> 00:59:26,059
My wife left me three months ago.

619
00:59:27,781 --> 00:59:30,534
God, l'm such a mess.

620
00:59:30,701 --> 00:59:33,420
Can't work, can't sleep.

621
00:59:43,501 --> 00:59:45,332
Richard, don't cry.

622
00:59:47,101 --> 00:59:49,251
I'm sure it's what's best for her.

623
00:59:49,421 --> 00:59:51,173
-And you.
-I need you!

624
00:59:51,341 --> 00:59:52,456
Richard, stop!

625
00:59:59,821 --> 01:00:01,493
I'm sorry.

626
01:00:01,701 --> 01:00:02,850
I'm sorry.

627
01:00:04,141 --> 01:00:05,733
I don't know what came over me.

628
01:00:05,901 --> 01:00:08,461
Maybe l misunderstood the situation
this weekend.

629
01:00:08,621 --> 01:00:10,691
I'm sorry if you thought
that we were. . . .

630
01:00:10,861 --> 01:00:13,250
-This is awkward.
-Just forget it happened.

631
01:00:13,421 --> 01:00:16,970
-Don't tell anybody l cried, okay?
-Okay.

632
01:00:17,541 --> 01:00:19,099
Good night.

633
01:00:32,021 --> 01:00:35,013
About the time she fell asleep,
l stopped kidding myself.

634
01:00:35,421 --> 01:00:37,730
I was nuts about her.

635
01:00:42,701 --> 01:00:45,340
Why couldn 't l have met her a year ago?

636
01:00:45,861 --> 01:00:47,658
Probably would have messed it up.

637
01:00:47,821 --> 01:00:50,938
Right here. Set it down.
Quick. Hurry up.

638
01:00:51,101 --> 01:00:53,615
Yeah. Got it.

639
01:00:55,701 --> 01:00:57,419
-Wait a minute, George.
-What?

640
01:00:57,581 --> 01:01:01,051
Just pin my arms down.
Good. Okay.

641
01:01:01,901 --> 01:01:05,132
Wait a minute.
Could you just squeeze my butt?

642
01:01:05,301 --> 01:01:07,940
Yeah. That's it.
Okay.

643
01:01:08,821 --> 01:01:11,289
Wait a minute. No, George. . . .

644
01:01:11,661 --> 01:01:13,140
-Oh, l'm sorry.
-God.

645
01:01:13,301 --> 01:01:15,053
Fate was cruel.

646
01:01:15,221 --> 01:01:17,735
Well, that was memorable.

647
01:01:17,981 --> 01:01:20,097
Just give me 1 0 minutes.

648
01:01:20,261 --> 01:01:22,217
Look at the moon or something.

649
01:01:24,981 --> 01:01:27,734
That night, l moved to the house
down the beach.

650
01:01:39,701 --> 01:01:42,818
The next day, l decided to call her.

651
01:01:47,221 --> 01:01:48,893
Hello?

652
01:01:50,341 --> 01:01:51,933
Hello?

653
01:01:52,101 --> 01:01:54,171
-Alice?
-Yes.

654
01:01:54,341 --> 01:01:55,979
I need to talk to you.

655
01:01:56,141 --> 01:01:57,415
Who is this?

656
01:01:57,581 --> 01:02:00,698
It's Nick. Nick Halloway.
Remember me?

657
01:02:00,861 --> 01:02:03,091
Nick Halloway. Is this a joke?

658
01:02:04,461 --> 01:02:07,100
Listen, please don't tell anybody.

659
01:02:07,261 --> 01:02:09,650
I'm in the gray-and-white house
down the beach.

660
01:02:09,821 --> 01:02:11,971
I'll leave the door open for you.

661
01:02:12,141 --> 01:02:14,609
Can you come down here, please?

662
01:02:15,021 --> 01:02:16,773
Please, Alice.

663
01:02:49,381 --> 01:02:51,099
Hello?

664
01:02:54,261 --> 01:02:56,092
Hello?

665
01:02:57,101 --> 01:02:58,819
Back here.

666
01:02:59,141 --> 01:03:00,699
Nick?

667
01:03:16,781 --> 01:03:20,774
Alice, don't be afraid.
It's me, Nick.

668
01:03:23,821 --> 01:03:27,496
-Were you in an accident?
-Yeah.

669
01:03:28,101 --> 01:03:30,854
Oh, what happened?
Were you burned or something?

670
01:03:31,021 --> 01:03:32,693
You want to sit down?

671
01:03:33,541 --> 01:03:35,020
No.

672
01:03:53,061 --> 01:03:55,291
Where the hell did she run to?
Bodega Bay?

673
01:03:55,461 --> 01:03:56,814
It's been over two hours.

674
01:03:56,981 --> 01:03:59,814
You never know.
Attractive girl, jogging alone.

675
01:03:59,981 --> 01:04:04,259
I wouldn't worry about that, George.
She's as strong as an ox.

676
01:04:10,821 --> 01:04:13,813
I will not allow you to turn this
into another fiasco. . .

677
01:04:13,981 --> 01:04:16,859
-. . .Iike you did in lran.
-I'm getting the job done.

678
01:04:17,021 --> 01:04:19,740
I'm your section head!
l gave you this chance!

679
01:04:19,901 --> 01:04:23,814
Wachs was supposed to be
in Washington two days ago.

680
01:04:23,981 --> 01:04:26,370
-Where the hell is he?
-Wachs is sequestered.

681
01:04:26,541 --> 01:04:30,853
I'm not convinced he's been entirely
forthcoming with us. Now calm down.

682
01:04:31,021 --> 01:04:32,818
Trust me.

683
01:04:33,461 --> 01:04:35,850
All right. When do l get him?

684
01:04:36,021 --> 01:04:37,454
-When l'm convinced.
-No.

685
01:04:37,621 --> 01:04:42,570
-When do l get the invisible man?
-He may be here still, but l doubt it.

686
01:04:42,741 --> 01:04:46,450
-I'll get him soon. Very soon.
-I hope so. It's my ass on the line.

687
01:04:46,621 --> 01:04:50,694
I won't justify these expenditures
and methods with no results!

688
01:04:50,861 --> 01:04:52,931
I want him, and if l don't get him. . .

689
01:04:53,101 --> 01:04:56,457
. . .you will be the next person
to disappear.

690
01:04:56,621 --> 01:04:59,658
Perhaps a reminder of the state of things
might be in order.

691
01:04:59,821 --> 01:05:02,540
I'm the one that kills people, Warren.
Not you.

692
01:05:02,701 --> 01:05:05,090
And if you screw up on me. . .

693
01:05:05,461 --> 01:05:08,100
. . .I will cut off your testicles,
fry them. . .

694
01:05:08,261 --> 01:05:11,571
. . .and Morrissey here
will have them for lunch.

695
01:05:22,061 --> 01:05:26,373
Nick, maybe this isn't
the right thing to do.

696
01:05:26,541 --> 01:05:30,011
Running and hiding.
Maybe you should be in the hospital.

697
01:05:30,181 --> 01:05:31,739
Not a chance.

698
01:05:31,901 --> 01:05:33,892
They know every move l make.

699
01:05:34,061 --> 01:05:37,497
Besides, there's nothing a doctor can do.
I feel normal.

700
01:05:39,101 --> 01:05:42,173
I probably could use a shave,
but who's gonna notice?

701
