Good evening. Two for dinner?

764
01:10:06,661 --> 01:10:07,980
Yes, please.

765
01:10:10,461 --> 01:10:12,656
What's the matter?
ls something wrong?

766
01:10:13,621 --> 01:10:16,658
Of course not, sir. Right this way.

767
01:10:21,981 --> 01:10:25,496
See? Nobody's staring at you.

768
01:10:25,661 --> 01:10:28,937
Whatever they think, they certainly
don't think you're invisible.

769
01:10:29,101 --> 01:10:30,375
No.

770
01:10:31,261 --> 01:10:34,333
They're just seeing a beautiful blond
and a dead man.

771
01:10:35,701 --> 01:10:36,929
To Elvis.

772
01:10:47,501 --> 01:10:49,492
Oh, God.

773
01:10:49,661 --> 01:10:52,175
Maybe we do have
a little more work to do.

774
01:10:56,621 --> 01:10:59,897
You can go to any ball game
or movie for free.

775
01:11:00,381 --> 01:11:04,215
You can look up girls' skirts,
hang around ladies' locker rooms.

776
01:11:05,421 --> 01:11:09,300
-Go naked anytime you want.
-Almost have to now.

777
01:11:09,461 --> 01:11:14,012
Never worry about people saying
you look older or you should lose weight.

778
01:11:14,781 --> 01:11:17,818
You could have a brilliant career
as a bank robber.

779
01:11:20,581 --> 01:11:22,856
Jesus, l'm screwed.

780
01:11:25,061 --> 01:11:26,699
Nick. . .

781
01:11:28,341 --> 01:11:30,332
. . .I've been thinking.

782
01:11:31,141 --> 01:11:33,575
I'm not sure me playing
the stock market. . .

783
01:11:33,741 --> 01:11:38,053
. . .so you can live like a recluse
is the best solution to your problem.

784
01:11:38,701 --> 01:11:41,773
You got a better idea, Alice,
believe me, l'm interested.

785
01:11:41,941 --> 01:11:46,173
We could go to Washington. I know
some people who might be able to help.

786
01:11:46,381 --> 01:11:49,498
You expect me to trust a politician?

787
01:11:50,221 --> 01:11:52,177
No, you're right.

788
01:11:53,581 --> 01:11:55,811
But l want you to trust me.

789
01:11:58,381 --> 01:12:00,656
You're not alone anymore.

790
01:12:17,421 --> 01:12:18,854
Come on!

791
01:12:33,301 --> 01:12:36,771
It's them. My clothes
are on the corner of the couch.

792
01:12:42,861 --> 01:12:45,978
-Where are we going?
-Far away. Fast.

793
01:13:14,981 --> 01:13:17,051
May l have your attention, please?

794
01:13:17,221 --> 01:13:20,452
Announcing the departure
of train number seven....

795
01:13:39,301 --> 01:13:41,974
-Nick?
-I'm here.

796
01:13:47,341 --> 01:13:50,731
I got us a compartment
on the 7:30 train to San Diego.

797
01:13:50,901 --> 01:13:55,053
From there, we can figure out
how to get across the border to Mexico.

798
01:13:55,621 --> 01:13:58,613
That gives us about eight hours to kill.

799
01:13:59,181 --> 01:14:03,015
Look, they're gonna catch me, Alice.
Just get on the train. Go.

800
01:14:03,181 --> 01:14:05,251
Get away from me.
These guys are nuts.

801
01:14:05,421 --> 01:14:08,094
I'd never forgive myself
if something happened to you.

802
01:14:08,261 --> 01:14:12,300
I'm not scared. Whoever these guys are,
they can't control everything.

803
01:14:12,461 --> 01:14:15,578
God, l can't believe l got you into this.

804
01:14:15,741 --> 01:14:17,333
Forgive me.

805
01:14:17,581 --> 01:14:20,095
This is something l have to do
on my own.

806
01:14:33,781 --> 01:14:35,055
Alice. . .

807
01:14:35,221 --> 01:14:37,576
. . .you're staring at my eyes.

808
01:14:38,781 --> 01:14:41,249
I think we should get out of the rain.

809
01:14:47,821 --> 01:14:49,413
What's happening to me?

810
01:14:49,581 --> 01:14:51,219
Don't.

811
01:14:52,181 --> 01:14:54,172
It's beautiful.

812
01:15:10,421 --> 01:15:14,130
Boy, how am l gonna tell my mom
about this?

813
01:15:16,781 --> 01:15:19,295
All the dirty parts l'd leave out.

814
01:15:20,821 --> 01:15:23,893
Just tell her you met a guy,
like him a lot. . .

815
01:15:24,061 --> 01:15:27,576
. . .could be serious. He's transparent.

816
01:15:29,901 --> 01:15:32,938
-Are you a Catholic?
-No.

817
01:15:33,101 --> 01:15:35,331
That could be a problem.

818
01:15:39,541 --> 01:15:41,418
You know something, Alice?

819
01:15:42,181 --> 01:15:45,253
If you were blind,
we'd make the perfect couple.

820
01:15:54,101 --> 01:15:56,137
May l have your attention, please?

821
01:15:56,301 --> 01:16:01,580
Now ready for departure,
train number 12, Pacific Coast....

822
01:16:05,301 --> 01:16:08,259
--now leaving on track number five.

823
01:16:09,341 --> 01:16:10,820
I'm in.

824
01:16:17,421 --> 01:16:19,332
That was easy enough.

825
01:16:25,421 --> 01:16:27,696
This isn't so bad.

826
01:16:33,221 --> 01:16:35,815
I'm having second thoughts about Mexico.

827
01:16:35,981 --> 01:16:38,449
It's just not far enough away.

828
01:16:39,301 --> 01:16:42,691
With a fax and a computer,
l can trade from anywhere in the world.

829
01:16:42,861 --> 01:16:46,297
You mean anywhere?
Like Paris, Rome. . .

830
01:16:46,981 --> 01:16:47,970
. . .Bora Bora?

831
01:16:49,341 --> 01:16:51,297
Anywhere you want.

832
01:17:08,941 --> 01:17:11,136
Although l was thinking of Switzerland.

833
01:17:11,301 --> 01:17:14,771
A guy can get away with wearing
a ski mask all year round.

834
01:17:25,101 --> 01:17:26,693
Where's the next stop?

835
01:17:42,861 --> 01:17:44,340
Nick?

836
01:17:45,381 --> 01:17:47,611
-You asleep?
-No.

837
01:17:49,301 --> 01:17:52,259
I was just daydreaming
about a New York strip steak. . .

838
01:17:52,421 --> 01:17:56,539
. . .baked potato with sour cream
and chives and a hot fudge sundae.

839
01:17:56,701 --> 01:17:58,896
That sounds great.

840
01:17:59,341 --> 01:18:03,937
I'll go get it.
Bring back a bowl of Jell-O for you.

841
01:18:08,141 --> 01:18:09,415
Thanks.

842
01:18:31,661 --> 01:18:33,538
Hello, Alice.

843
01:18:43,981 --> 01:18:45,937
Compartment C.

844
01:19:00,381 --> 01:19:01,780
Run!

845
01:19:01,941 --> 01:19:03,659
Nick!

846
01:19:03,821 --> 01:19:05,300
Run!

847
01:19:07,101 --> 01:19:08,454
Run!

848
01:19:11,341 --> 01:19:13,730
-Run!
-Halloway!

849
01:19:15,141 --> 01:19:16,620
Alice!

850
01:19:34,341 --> 01:19:36,935
Move! Move!
Get out of the way!

851
01:19:47,941 --> 01:19:49,579
No!

852
01:19:58,381 --> 01:20:01,578
The current must have swept me along
for half a mile.

853
01:20:01,861 --> 01:20:04,659
When l came to, l was being washed
toward a drainage pipe...

854
01:20:04,821 --> 01:20:06,971
...and throwing up a gallon
of river water.

855
01:20:13,621 --> 01:20:17,739
For all you knew, l'd drowned.
Your invisible man was dead.

856
01:20:17,901 --> 01:20:20,461
But l knew you had Alice.

857
01:20:25,421 --> 01:20:29,050
I was wrong to involve her in
the first place, Just like l was wrong...

858
01:20:29,221 --> 01:20:31,257
... thinking l could run away from this.

859
01:20:31,421 --> 01:20:34,060
I am what l am, Jenkins.
I know that now.

860
01:20:34,221 --> 01:20:36,496
Other people will too,
unless you let her go.

861
01:20:36,661 --> 01:20:40,017
You let her go, l'll come in.
That's the deal.

862
01:20:40,541 --> 01:20:42,418
I'll say this.

863
01:20:43,021 --> 01:20:45,819
Your friend Halloway
has a flair for the dramatic.

864
01:20:48,421 --> 01:20:51,413
I want you to be part of our team, Alice.

865
01:20:52,381 --> 01:20:54,212
He needs you. We need you.

866
01:20:54,821 --> 01:21:00,134
Regardless of how it may seem, l've never
had anything but his best interest at heart.

867
01:21:00,781 --> 01:21:03,818
Where do they find people like you?

868
01:21:04,461 --> 01:21:06,691
It's him. He's on the phone.

869
01:21:12,781 --> 01:21:14,055
Nick.

870
01:21:14,221 --> 01:21:17,736
I've got copies of that tape
in very safe hands right now.

871
01:21:17,901 --> 01:21:21,735
Anything happens to Alice,
they go to the networks, the papers.

872
01:21:21,901 --> 01:21:23,619
Use your imagination.

873
01:21:23,781 --> 01:21:27,490
Alice is here. She's absolutely fine.
What do you want me to do?

874
01:21:27,661 --> 01:21:31,017
