881
01:21:49,181 --> 01:21:52,014
Two minutes, Jenkins, starting now.

882
01:21:53,141 --> 01:21:54,130
Let's go.

883
01:22:08,901 --> 01:22:12,610
-I presume you've seen this.
-He's outside. We're five seconds away.

884
01:22:12,781 --> 01:22:15,932
-You murdered Wachs?
-He's holding me against my will.

885
01:22:16,101 --> 01:22:20,572
We've won, Warren. He's ours.
We can own the agency.

886
01:22:20,741 --> 01:22:23,653
You've lost it.
You don't know what you're doing.

887
01:22:23,821 --> 01:22:28,576
-I'm pulling the plug. Let her go!
-As soon as we make the switch.

888
01:22:45,701 --> 01:22:48,010
Just like we agreed, Nick.

889
01:22:49,061 --> 01:22:51,939
-Get the cab, Tyler.
-Yes, sir.

890
01:23:02,741 --> 01:23:05,096
Nick, l love you!

891
01:23:06,301 --> 01:23:09,418
Take her across the bridge
or something. Go!

892
01:23:31,621 --> 01:23:33,816
We had a deal, Nick.

893
01:23:34,181 --> 01:23:36,456
You shouldn't have tried to run.

894
01:23:39,181 --> 01:23:41,741
Hey, not so rough.

895
01:23:41,901 --> 01:23:43,573
Jesus.

896
01:23:51,181 --> 01:23:52,773
Where's Nick?

897
01:23:58,701 --> 01:24:00,612
Wait a minute.
Where are we going?

898
01:24:00,781 --> 01:24:02,612
The Bay Bridge.

899
01:24:03,941 --> 01:24:05,977
And l love you too.

900
01:24:07,301 --> 01:24:08,814
Nick?

901
01:24:09,221 --> 01:24:12,657
Nick. Oh, my God!

902
01:24:12,821 --> 01:24:14,174
Oh, look out.

903
01:24:14,341 --> 01:24:17,890
That was George in the phone booth.
I called Jenkins with this.

904
01:24:18,061 --> 01:24:20,450
-You told George you were invisible?
-Of course not.

905
01:24:20,621 --> 01:24:24,136
Told him you we're in trouble.
Asked him for a big favor.

906
01:24:24,301 --> 01:24:26,371
God, l'm glad you're all right.

907
01:24:34,781 --> 01:24:36,578
I got him.

908
01:24:53,581 --> 01:24:56,141
-Are you all right?
-Yes.

909
01:24:56,781 --> 01:24:59,420
Nick, run! Run!

910
01:25:01,461 --> 01:25:03,019
Help!

911
01:25:03,181 --> 01:25:04,853
Help!

912
01:25:16,621 --> 01:25:19,579
I've got him crossing Seventh Street
back toward Market.

913
01:25:26,381 --> 01:25:28,611
-Market Street.
-It's over!

914
01:25:28,781 --> 01:25:32,456
You hear me? l'm shutting you down!
l'm shutting you down!

915
01:25:44,861 --> 01:25:47,329
-He's heading south.
-Left on Fifth.

916
01:25:47,501 --> 01:25:51,130
Look. What about what Singleton said?
He signs the checks.

917
01:25:51,301 --> 01:25:54,213
Screw him. He's weak.
They're all weak.

918
01:25:54,381 --> 01:25:58,852
Think what Halloway will fetch.
The Germans, the Japanese, the Saudis.

919
01:25:59,181 --> 01:26:00,853
You'll be a rich man, Morrissey.

920
01:26:32,541 --> 01:26:35,180
Oh, my God! Look at that!

921
01:26:36,021 --> 01:26:37,693
What was that?

922
01:27:50,701 --> 01:27:53,898
You're a natural, you know.
Cool, imaginative, elegant.

923
01:27:54,781 --> 01:27:56,533
You've found your calling, Nick.

924
01:27:57,541 --> 01:28:01,978
I think we can work this thing out
together, you and l. Forgive and forget.

925
01:28:02,141 --> 01:28:07,169
Start again fresh, with a deeper sense
of respect for each other.

926
01:28:17,101 --> 01:28:19,934
Nick, l'll kill you if l have to!

927
01:28:23,661 --> 01:28:25,413
Now listen.

928
01:28:26,181 --> 01:28:29,969
I'll commit every resource we have
to getting you back. . .

929
01:28:30,141 --> 01:28:32,257
. . .to making you whole again. . .

930
01:28:32,421 --> 01:28:35,458
. . .to reuniting you with Alice.
