a second ago.

932
01:28:37,821 --> 01:28:41,018
I think you're losing your marbles, Dave.
Get it straight.

933
01:29:00,461 --> 01:29:02,736
Bit of a tight spot, Nick.

934
01:29:03,861 --> 01:29:05,692
Now, understand. . .

935
01:29:06,341 --> 01:29:08,457
. . .if l can't have you. . .

936
01:29:08,701 --> 01:29:10,578
. . .no one can.

937
01:29:12,941 --> 01:29:14,977
I'm tired of the game, Dave.

938
01:29:16,461 --> 01:29:19,373
One step back, and it's all over.

939
01:29:19,781 --> 01:29:21,009
Now wait.

940
01:29:21,381 --> 01:29:24,373
I apologize for being rash.
It was stupid of me.

941
01:29:25,101 --> 01:29:29,060
You are the most unique human being
on the planet.

942
01:29:29,221 --> 01:29:31,496
You are walking history.

943
01:29:31,901 --> 01:29:34,699
Don't run away from it, man.
Embrace it!

944
01:29:41,461 --> 01:29:43,338
You'll never know what it's like.

945
01:29:43,501 --> 01:29:46,299
Don't. Now, don't, Nick.

946
01:29:47,021 --> 01:29:49,216
Don't come any closer!

947
01:29:49,421 --> 01:29:51,616
Come on, Nick.
Just give me your hand.

948
01:29:51,781 --> 01:29:54,500
-No! No! No!
-Give me your hand.

949
01:29:55,981 --> 01:29:58,449
Olé, you son of a bitch!

950
01:29:59,981 --> 01:30:01,334
Nick!

951
01:30:22,861 --> 01:30:26,137
Leave it alone. You didn't see anything.
You don't know anything.

952
01:30:26,301 --> 01:30:29,771
You didn't hear any of this.
Be smart.

953
01:30:31,341 --> 01:30:33,935
Clean it up. It never happened.

954
01:30:45,301 --> 01:30:47,974
-What did you lose, a contact lens?
-Nick!

955
01:30:48,141 --> 01:30:50,860
Don't say anything.
Let's just get out of here.

956
01:30:51,021 --> 01:30:53,455
-Look sad.
-Okay.

957
01:30:56,221 --> 01:30:58,860
My department had been alerted
to Mr. Jenkins' . . .

958
01:30:59,021 --> 01:31:01,330
. . .deteriorating emotional state.

959
01:31:01,501 --> 01:31:04,618
Of course, none of us
ever expected a tragedy like this.

960
01:31:04,781 --> 01:31:07,659
I think you can all appreciate how. . . .

961
01:31:09,741 --> 01:31:12,460
Oh, Nick.
I never want to lose you.

962
01:31:12,621 --> 01:31:14,816
You won't. I promise.

963
01:31:14,981 --> 01:31:18,053
It's keeping track of our kids
that's got me worried.

964
